Jonny Wilkinson is an extremely calm, reserved and quiet individual - although not in the changing room it appears!

The ex-England fly half, who dropped the winning goal in the 2003 World Cup final, claimed both the Heineken Cup and the Top 14 titles with Toulon last season before retiring.

And, in a promotional video ahead of the release of a DVD showcasing the French side's magnificent double-winning season, Wilkinson is seen giving a passionate - and expletive-laden - team talk during half-time of the Top 14 semi-final against Racing Metro at Stade Pierre-Mauroy.

